   Ades said Tuesday he hadn't spoken to the AP at all.
</P>
<P>
   The story was based on a phone call with a person who identified
himself as Ades to an AP sports reporter.
</P>
<P>
   AP sports editor Terry Taylor said the news agency was checking
the source of the call.
</P>
<P>
   Jarvis issued a statement Tuesday saying he has ''no interest in
any other college coaching job.''
</P>
<P>
   ''Anything that is said, in regards to any job regarding Mike
Jarvis, will be made by me and only me,'' Jarvis said. ''The
statements that are attributed to Rob Ades are false and
inaccurate.''
</P>
<P>
   Jarvis had been discussing the Wizards job with Jordan.
</P>
