<HEADLINE> Motorcycle accidents kills 24-year-old  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   MOREAU, N.Y. (AP) -- A 24-year-old New York City man died after
crashing his motorcycle into a telephone pole, according to the
Saratoga County Sheriff's department.
</P>
<P>
   Jason M. Sokol was traveling west Monday when his motorcycle
went off the side of the highway in Saratoga County and struck the
pole. There were no other vehicles involved in the accident.
