<HEADLINE> Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   In the birthday spotlight:
</P>
<P>
   Alanis Morissette, Metallica, Patti Smith, James Brown, Beck and
Bo Diddley are booked for a three-day music festival kicking off
the opening of Paul Allen's new rock museum in Seattle. The
festival begins June 23. Morissette, who was born on June 1, 1974,
played the role of God in Kevin Smith's controversial film
''Dogma.'' Her album ''Supposed Former Infatuation Junkie'' was
honored as album of the year at the Juno Awards, the Canadian
equivalent of the Grammys.
</P>
<P>
   Rupert Everett, who was born on May 29, 1959, starred with
Madonna in the recent film ''The Next Best Thing.'' Madonna played
a yoga instructor who became pregnant after a drunken night with
gay friend Everett. Besides starring in the film, Everett provided
distant background vocals for Madonna's version of Don McLean's
1971 classic ''American Pie,'' one of the songs in the movie.
</P>
<P>
   This year's American Country Music Award for vocal event of the
year went to Clint Black and his actress-wife Lisa Hartman Black.
The couple won for the duet ''When I Said I Do.'' Hartman Black was
one of the stars of the nighttime soap opera ''Knots Landing,''
which ran from 1979 to 1993. Black said it ''was a true awards show
moment'' for him to see his wife's face when their names were
called. Hartman Black was born on June 1, 1956.
</P>
<P>
   Celebrity birthdays for May 28-June 3:
</P>
<P>
   May 28: Singer Gladys Knight is 56. Singer John Fogerty is 55.
Rapper Chubb Rock is 32. Actor Glenn Quinn (''Angel'') is 30.
</P>
<P>
   May 29: Comedian Bob Hope is 97. Actor Kevin Conway is 58.
Singer LaToya Jackson is 44. Actress Annette Bening is 42. Actor
Rupert Everett is 41. Singer Melissa Etheridge is 39. Actress Lisa
Whelchel (''The Facts of Life'') is 37. Singer Melanie Brown (Mel
B./Scary Spice) of Spice Girls is 25. Rapper Playa Poncho is 25.
</P>
<P>
   May 30: Actor Michael J. Pollard is 61. Country singer Wynonna
is 36. Musician Patrick Dahlheimer of Live is 29. Rapper Cee-Lo
with Goodie Mob is 26.
</P>
<P>
   May 31: Actor-director Clint Eastwood is 70. Actor Keir Dullea
(''2001: A Space Odyssey'') is 64. Singer Peter Yarrow of Peter,
Paul and Mary is 62. Actress Sharon Gless (''Cagney and Lacey'') is
57. Actor Gregory Harrison is 50. Actor Tom Berenger is 50.
Actor-comedian Chris Elliott is 40. Actor Kyle Secor (''Homicide:
Life on the Street'') is 40. Actress Lea Thompson (''Caroline in
the City'') is 39. Rapper Kid Frost is 36. Rapper DMC of Run-DMC is
36. Actress Brooke Shields is 35.
</P>
<P>
   June 1: Actor Andy Griffith is 74. Actor Edward Woodward (''The
Equalizer'') is 70. Singer Pat Boone is 66. Actor Morgan Freeman is
63. Actor Rene Auberjonois (''Star Trek: Deep Space Nine'') is 60.
Musician Ron Wood of the Rolling Stones is 53. Singer Graham
Russell of Air Supply is 50. Country singer Ronnie Dunn of Brooks
and Dunn is 47. Actress Lisa Hartman Black is 44. Singer Alanis
Morissette is 26.
</P>
