<HEADLINE> Entertainment Highlights in History  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Entertainment highlights during the week of May
28-June 3:
<TEXT>
<P>
   45 years ago: Marilyn Monroe and Tom Ewell starred in ''The
Seven Year Itch.''
</P>
<P>
   35 years ago: Bob Dylan's ''Bringing It All Back Home'' topped
the British album chart, replacing ''Freewheelin' Bob Dylan'' in
the top spot.
</P>
<P>
   25 years ago: The Rolling Stones began a tour of the United
States in Baton Rouge, La. It was the Stones' first tour with
guitarist Ron Wood.
</P>
<P>
   15 years ago: Comedian Bob Hope celebrated his 82nd birthday by
christening a building named after him as headquarters of the
United Service Organization in Washington, D.C. ''I always knew I'd
have a building named after me in Washington, but I thought it
would be the IRS building,'' Hope quipped.
</P>
<P>
   10 years ago: ''Seinfeld,'' starring comedian Jerry Seinfeld,
made its debut. The premiere of the half-hour series on NBC was
ranked No. 3 by the A.C. Nielsen Co.
</P>
<P>
   ''Total Recall,'' starring Arnold Schwarzenegger, opened in
theaters nationwide. The film grossed more than $25 million during
its first three days of release.
</P>
<P>
   Actor Michael Douglas won the third annual Spencer Tracy Award,
joining William Hurt and Jimmy Stewart as recipients of the honor
praising standard-setting performances.
</P>
<P>
   And Australian band Midnight Oil gave a free concert in midtown
Manhattan in response to the oil spill of the Exxon Valdez in
Alaska. The band was on a U.S. tour to promote its new album ''Blue
Sky Mining.''
</P>
<P>
   Five years ago: Guitarist Ted Nugent placed his handprint and
signature in cement in the Hollywood Rock Walk of Fame.
</P>
<P>
   And Bob Hope celebrated his 92nd birthday by attending a
ceremony in New Orleans to lay the keel of the USNS Bob Hope, a
support vessel. ''You know, in the past 40 or 50 years, I've seen
the Navy everywhere in the world and they've always been very kind
to me,'' Hope told some 400 people attending the ceremony. Hope
spent years entertaining U.S. troops.
</P>
<P>
   One year ago: Blues guitarist B.B. King was named entertainer of
the year at the 20th annual W.C. Handy Blues Awards. King also won
contemporary blues album of the year for ''Blues on the Bayou.''
</P>
<P>
   And the Royal Swedish Academy of Music picked Stevie Wonder and
composer Iannis Xenakis as the 1999 winners of the Polar Music
Prize.
</P>
<P>
   Spoken five years ago:
</P>
<P>
   ''I started to cut down 10 years ago -- getting off the port and
brandies because I had a vocal coach who said, 'You're just ruining
your voice.' I've found a drink now -- rum and coke. If I have a rum
and coke before I go on and a couple halfway through the show, it
doesn't have any effect at all.'' -- Rocker Rod Stewart.
</P>
<P>
   Spoken one year ago:
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm trying to get it together. I stopped doing a lot of things
-- I won't drink and I don't smoke. But I don't want people to be
like, 'OK, now she's Reverend Elliott.'' -- Rapper Missy
''Misdemeanor'' Elliott.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-05-24-00 1313 </TRAILER>
