<HEADLINE> 15-year-old in serious condition following school hallway stabbing  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- A 15-year-old city boy was in serious
condition with abdominal wounds Wednesday following a stabbing by
another teen in a high school hallway.
</P>
<P>
   Police say 14-year-old Matthew Blanding apparently stabbed
Donald Murdoch with a leatherman utility knife three times before
hall monitors at Albany High School could break up the 1:20 p.m.
fight outside the school's library.
</P>
<P>
   Blanding was in the Capital Region Juvenile Detention Facility.
He was arraigned Wednesday on first-degree assault and criminal
possession of a weapon. He is being charged as an adult.
</P>
<P>
   School officials said they were reviewing videotapes of the
fight.
</P>
